val: Have you felt productive in your work?
Do you enjoy participating in school and/or work activities?
Have you noticed higher stress level in your life?
Have you felt out of control and powerless in your life?
Have you found yourself distancing from your friends and family?
Have you felt increase in headaches and/or lack of sleep?
Have you felt these symptoms for a long period of time?

Honeymoon Phase: This stage is categorized by high satisfaction in your current situation. You are more likely to feel energetic and creative in your work. At this stage, it is best to create positive coping strategies to deal with any ongoing stress.

Onset of Stress: At this stage, you are most likely experiencing a few bad days in the week. You may have noticed an increase in job and/or work dissatisfaction, work inefficiency and escapist activities (overeating, drinking, smoking, etc.).

Chronic Stress: If youâ€™re at this stage, you have probably noticed the physical side effects of stress. You most likely felt severe headaches, digestive problems, chronic exhaustion, and/or physical illnesses. Your work ethic may be at an all-time low, with problem-solving skills and performance decreasing. It may even be harder to control your emotional state, often lashing out at others or experiencing depressive episodes.

Burnout: At this stage, your symptoms may become severe to the point where you find it difficult to function. You may have experienced an increase in the feeling of failure and powerlessness. You may become indifferent to work and/or school. Any physical symptoms may intensify or increase in number.

Habitual Burnout: This stage is similar to burnout, with symptoms such as feelings of failure, indifference to work, physical illnesses, and fatigue. However, these symptoms of burnout may have become embedded in your life, acting as a habit.
